Subject:      Re: Zen & lango
 
John Geraets--
 
On Zen & poetry & Leslie Scalapino.  Funny you should ask.  You might
want to take a look at the writing of Norman Fischer (recently
elevated to the status of zen abbot -- based in San Francisco).  His
most recent book, from Chax, PRECISELY THE POINT BEING MADE,
is quite marvelous.  And zen-nish.  I mention Norman in connection
with Leslie because the two of them are currently writing back and
forth, a series of poems and letters that definitely do push & pull
around zen practice.  You might try writing directly to Leslie
Scalapino or to Norman if you're interested in looking at this
exchange-in-progress.
 
Hank Lazer
