In Canada it is not unlikely to find that men who work with wood also
read (and write) poetry. David Phillips is a terrific poet who works
as a carpenter. Bob Fones is a very good poet who works as a
carpenter. Bob Rose (who has moved back to Wash. State) is a good
poet and carpenter, and here in Vancouver once workt at a wooden
shipworks. I have poems by and bookshelves by both Rose and Phillips
in my house.
