From:         Charles Alexander <mcba@MAROON.TC.UMN.EDU>
Subject:      Not all chance, not at all??
X-To:         UB@maroon.tc.umn.edu, Poetics@maroon.tc.umn.edu,
              Discussion@maroon.tc.umn.edu, Group@maroon.tc.umn.edu
 
In part trying out a new program for e-mail and more, in part thinking
about the conversations on aleatory composition, in part wanting more poems
on this forum, here:
 
 
This is the year 1997 and there
are gale winds in the west, never
a note played in discontent and
 
in a place where animals play
the imagined margins soar with letters
flung at odd intervals and ink
spills a clear running relevance
moved to safer particles, absolved.
 
These are the words the heart makes
forgetting its injunction to exercise
while floating, fingers succumb to
the temptation to imply themselves
or another, waiting, presumptive.
 
Do not argue, I want to say, there
is not enough time, I don't even know
what thought might bring the third day
and something beats now, wanting
only to be subject, object too, yours.
 
What will the hospital say, the treadmill,
another language of not knowing, as if
anything else were possible, today or
another time, invisible, flags from porches
forego the year, the skin, the tissue.
We are flying on the ground.
 
 
      charles alexander
 
charles alexander
chax press
minnesota center for book arts
phone & fax: 612-721-6063
e-mail: mcba@maroon.tc.umn.edu
