Maria & other interested parties --
here's the info. on that mag. I mentioned earlier --
 
the January/February 1994 issue (#99) of _New Observations_, guest edited
by Harry Mathews and Lynn Crawford, is a special "Oulipo * Oupeinpo" issue--
 
"Oupeinpo" stands for Ouvoir de Peinture Potentielle
 
lots of good stuff here -- my own favorite being Thieri Foulc's "New
Observations on Harry Mathew's Face"-- though Queneau's "The Foundations
of Literature" will be of special interest to those (and you know who you
are) who follow the study of mathematics and poetry.
