Dear Cris 'n Carl,
                Just to extend this to another generation of high thinking--
as in 'high steppin'' I took it--Sigmar Polke, and his famous HOHERE WESEN
BEFAHLEN: RECHTE OBERE ECKE SCHWARZ MALEN! (Higher Beings Command: Paint the
top right hand corner black!) c.1966. Apart from these words, the canvas is
blank except for its black corner on the top right. he also did a painting
of flamingos which was accompanied by the following text ( it was in german)
       I stood in front of the canvas and tried to paint a bunch of
       flowers. Then I received fromhigher beings the command: No
       bunches of flowers! Paint flamingos! At first I tried to continue
       painting. But then I realised that they meant business.
 
Wystan
