 "How much Real is transformed
via poetry?"
 
Poetry is the unfolding courses of the real. Jack Foley, in his STANZAS FROM
DJERASSI says,
 
to stay
at the edge
of blackness
to
keep
faith
with
light
 
Poetry is the real projecting in one of the million directions into the
unknown, shedding light, advancing outward. Poetry is the real at the
threshold, authenticity before reality checks in.
